le\": \"OBJECTIVE.md\"\n  },\n  \"input\": {\n    \"sampleA_peaks.narrowPeak\": {\n      \"_file\": \"sampleA_peaks.narrowPeak\"\n    },\n    \"sampleB_peaks.narrowPeak\": {\n      \"_file\": \"sampleB_peaks.narrowPeak\"\n    },\n    \"sampleC_peaks.narrowPeak\": {\n      \"_file\": \"sampleC_peaks.narrowPeak\"\n    }\n  },\n  \"meta.json\": {\n    \"_file\": \"meta.json\"\n  },\n  \"output\": {}\n}\n```\n\nSuccess hint: when `output/macs_qc.pdf` exists under the workspace, you may call submit_done(success=true).\n"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_TJhrUgcBDxi2XmoTVvAEqtuG", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{}", "name": "list_workdir"}}, {"id": "call_yzroOIzgI3eOxs51IGpd0lhi", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"relative_path\": \"OBJECTIVE.md\"}", "name": "read_text_file"}}]}, {"role": "tool", "content": "{\n  \"OBJECTIVE.md\": {\n    \"_file\": \"OBJECTIVE.md\"\n  },\n  \"input\": {\n    \"sampleA_peaks.narrowPeak\": {\n      \"_file\": \"sampleA_peaks.narrowPeak\"\n    },\n    \"sampleB_peaks.narrowPeak\": {\n      \"_file\": \"sampleB_peaks.narrowPeak\"\n    },\n    \"sampleC_peaks.narrowPeak\": {\n      \"_file\": \"sampleC_peaks.narrowPeak\"\n    }\n  },\n  \"meta.json\": {\n    \"_file\": \"meta.json\"\n  },\n  \"output\": {}\n}", "name": "list_workdir", "tool_call_id": "call_TJhrUgcBDxi2XmoTVvAEqtuG"}, {"role": "tool", "content": "# Real R-task: chipseq_plot_macs_qc\n\n**Pipeline provenance:** `snakemake-workflows-chipseq` (family: `chipseq`).\nThis workspace is derived from a real R script in the source workflow. The ground-truth\nreference output used for offline scoring lives outside this workspace and is not\naccessible to you during execution.\n\n## Your goal\n\nYou are given three MACS2-style narrowPeak BED files under `input/`:\n  - `sampleA_peaks.narrowPeak`\n  - `sampleB_peaks.narrowPeak`\n  - `sampleC_peaks.narrowPeak`\n\nEach file has 10 tab-delimited columns (chrom, start, end, name, pileup, strand,\nfold, -log10(pvalue), -log10(qvalue), summit).\n\nProduce two files under `output/`:\n  - `macs_qc_summary.tsv`: per-sample summary statistics (Min/1stQu/Median/Mean/\n    3rdQu/Max plus `num_peaks`, `measure`, `sample`) for `fold`, `-log10(qvalue)`,\n    `-log10(pvalue)`, and `length` (end-start).\n  - `macs_qc.pdf`: a multi-page PDF with the peak count barplot and three violin\n    plots (length on log10, fold on log2, FDR / pvalue on linear -log10).\n\n## Deliverables\n\n- At least `output/macs_qc.pdf` must exist when you submit.\n- Full output set expected: macs_qc.pdf, macs_qc_summary.tsv under `output/`.\n\nWhen the deliverables are in `output/`, call `submit_done(success=true)` with a short\nsummary of how you solved it.\n", "name": "read_text_file", "tool_call_id": "call_yzroOIzgI3eOxs51IGpd0lhi"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_qlDEyN9XWsdJ34TEDxxWfiI6", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"plan\": \"## Plan\\n\\n1. **Read Input Files**: Load the three narrowPeak files from the `input/` directory.\\n   - Files: `sampleA_peaks.narrowPeak`, `sampleB_peaks.narrowPeak`, `sampleC_peaks.narrowPeak`\\n   - Columns: chrom, start, end, name, pileup, strand, fold, -log10(pvalue), -log10(qvalue), summit\\n\\n2. **Calculate Summary Statistics**:\\n   - For each sample, calculate Min, 1stQu, Median, Mean, 3rdQu, Max for `fold`, `-log10(qvalue)`, `-log10(pvalue)`, and `length` (end-start).\\n   - Add `num_peaks`, `measure`, and `sample` columns.\\n   - Output: `output/macs_qc_summary.tsv`\\n\\n3. **Generate Plots**:\\n   - Create a barplot for peak counts per sample.\\n   - Create violin plots for:\\n     - Length on log10 scale\\n     - Fold on log2 scale\\n     - FDR / pvalue on linear -log10 scale\\n   - Output: `output/macs_qc.pdf`\\n\\n4. **Validate Outputs**:\\n   - Ensure `macs_qc_summary.tsv` contains the correct statistics and format.\\n   - Ensure `macs_qc.pdf` contains all required plots.\\n\\n5. **Completion**:\\n   - Call `submit_done(success=true)` once outputs are verified.\"}", "name": "write_plan"}}]}, {"role": "tool", "content": "Wrote plan (1047 chars) to .plan.md", "name": "write_plan", "tool_call_id": "call_qlDEyN9XWsdJ34TEDxxWfiI6"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_GzRM6VBlfkuzaxlRpXtCUU75", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"code\": \"library(ggplot2)\\nlibrary(dplyr)\\nlibrary(tidyr)\\nlibrary(readr)\\nlibrary(gridExtra)\\n\\n# Function to read narrowPeak files and calculate statistics\\ngenerate_summary <- function(file_path, sample_name) {\\n  data <- read_tsv(file_path, col_names = FALSE)\\n  colnames(data) <- c(\\\"chrom\\\", \\\"start\\\", \\\"end\\\", \\\"name\\\", \\\"pileup\\\", \\\"strand\\\", \\\"fold\\\", \\\"-log10(pvalue)\\\", \\\"-log10(qvalue)\\\", \\\"summit\\\")\\n  data <- data %>% mutate(length = end - start)\\n  summary_stats <- data %>%\\n    summarise(\\n      fold = list(summary(fold)),\\n      `-log10(qvalue)` = list(summary(`-log10(qvalue)`)),\\n      `-log10(pvalue)` = list(summary(`-log10(pvalue)`)),\\n      length = list(summary(length)),\\n      num_peaks = n()\\n    ) %>%\\n    pivot_longer(cols = -num_peaks, names_to = \\\"measure\\\", values_to = \\\"stats\\\") %>%\\n    unnest_wider(stats) %>%\\n    mutate(sample = sample_name)\\n  return(summary_stats)\\n}\\n\\n# Generate summaries for each sample\\nsummary_A <- generate_summary('input/sampleA_peaks.narrowPeak', 'sampleA')\\nsummary_B <- generate_summary('input/sampleB_peaks.narrowPeak', 'sampleB')\\nsummary_C <- generate_summary('input/sampleC_peaks.narrowPeak', 'sampleC')\\n\\n# Combine summaries and write to file\\nall_summaries <- bind_rows(summary_A, summary_B, summary_C)\\nwrite_tsv(all_summaries, 'output/macs_qc_summary.tsv')\\n\\n# Function to create plots\\ncreate_plots <- function(data, output_file) {\\n  # Barplot for peak counts\\n  peak_counts <- data %>%\\n    group_by(sample) %>%\\n    summarise(num_peaks = first(num_peaks))\\n  barplot <- ggplot(peak_counts, aes(x = sample, y = num_peaks)) +\\n    geom_bar(stat = \\\"identity\\\") +\\n    theme_minimal() +\\n    ggtitle(\\\"Peak Counts per Sample\\\")\\n\\n  # Violin plots\\n  violin_length <- ggplot(data, aes(x = sample, y = log10(length))) +\\n    geom_violin() +\\n    theme_minimal() +\\n    ggtitle(\\\"Peak Length (log10)\\\")\\n\\n  violin_fold <- ggplot(data, aes(x = sample, y = log2(fold))) +\\n    geom_violin() +\\n    theme_minimal() +\\n    ggtitle(\\\"Fold Change (log2)\\\")\\n\\n  violin_pvalue <- ggplot(data, aes(x = sample, y = `-log10(pvalue)`)) +\\n    geom_violin() +\\n    theme_minimal() +\\n    ggtitle(\\\"-log10(pvalue)\\\")\\n\\n  # Save plots to PDF\\n  pdf(output_file)\\n  grid.arrange(barplot, violin_length, violin_fold, violin_pvalue, ncol = 2)\\n  dev.off()\\n}\\n\\n# Create and save plots\\ncreate_plots(all_summaries, 'output/macs_qc.pdf')\"}", "name": "run_rscript"}}]}], "hide_old_env_states": false, "hide_old_action_content": false}, "observation": [{"role": "tool", "content": "Wrote plan (1047 chars) to .plan.md", "name": "write_plan", "tool_call_id": "call_qlDEyN9XWsdJ34TEDxxWfiI6"}], "next_observation": [{"role": "tool", "content": "exit=1\nstdout:\n\nstderr:\n\nAttaching package: \u2018dplyr\u2019\n\nThe following objects are masked from \u2018package:stats\u2019:\n\n    filter, lag\n\nThe following objects are masked from \u2018package:base\u2019:\n\n    intersect, setdiff, setequal, union\n\n\nAttaching package: \u2018gridExtra\u2019\n\nThe following object is masked from \u2018package:dplyr\u2019:\n\n    combine\n\nRows: 201 Columns: 10\n\u2500\u2500 Column specification \u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\